column20: "Freshly frozen tumor tissues were embedded in Optimal Cutting Temperature compound and stored at -80°C."
column22: "Tissue was cut in sections (10uM) using a cryostat. five sections (10 µm) were cut and used for RNA extraction. The five sections were transferred to RLT buffer using the RNeasy Mini Kit (Qiagen, Hilden, Germany) according to the manufacturer’s instructions. Samples were prepared for sequencing using Illumina TruSeq RNA Sample Prep Kit v2, using polyA selection. The sequencing was performed multiplexed with five samples per lane on Illumina HiSeq2500 machines (Illumina, San Diego, CA, USA) using the standard Illumina RNAseq protocol with a read length of 2 x 100 bases."
column23: "Libraries were prepared according to Illumina´s TruSeq strand-specific RNA kit."
column25: "Mapping of reads to GRCh37 reference genome using TopHat 2.0.8b with Bowtie 2.1.0. Default settings"
column26: "Abundance estiamtion (FPKM) using Cufflinks 2.1.1 with transcript annotation from Ensembl v73, Homo_sapiens.GRCh37.73.gtf Non-default settings: --max-bundle-frags 10000000 --max-bundle-length 10000000"
column27: "Raw read count estimation using featureCounts 1.4.0p1 with same GTF as above, Settings: -g gene_id -t exon"
column29: "Supplementary_files_format_and_content: Tab-separated matrices with FPKM and read counts, respectively"

The five sections were transferred to RLT buffer using the RNeasy Mini Kit (Qiagen, Hilden, Germany) according to the manufacturer’s instructions. Samples were prepared for sequencing using Illumina TruSeq RNA Sample Prep Kit v2, using polyA selection. The sequencing was performed multiplexed with five samples per lane on Illumina HiSeq2500 machines (Illumina, San Diego, CA, USA) using the standard Illumina RNAseq protocol with a read length of 2 x 100 bases."
column23: "Libraries were prepared according to Illumina´s TruSeq strand-specific RNA kit."
column25: "Mapping of reads to GRCh37 reference genome using TopHat 2.0.8b with Bowtie 2.1.0. Default settings"
column26: "Abundance estiamtion (FPKM) using Cufflinks 2.1.1 with transcript annotation from Ensembl v73, Homo_sapiens.GRCh37.73.gtf Non-default settings: --max-bundle-frags 10000000 --max-bundle-length 10000000"
column27: "Raw read count estimation using featureCounts 1.4.0p1 with same GTF as above, Settings: -g gene_id -t exon"
column29: "Supplementary_files_format_and_content: Tab-separated matrices with FPKM and read counts, respectively"
